node.text:
Do you want to play this fun word game with me? After you watch the video, come up with your own word and put it in the comments! It’s addicting!

This word building activity will engage all your students while teaching prefixes, suffixes, spelling patterns, and new vocabulary! You can use this as a center or partner work, enrichment homework, whole or small group instruction, or even a five minute filler! If the link in my profile doesn’t work because it’s a video, message me for the link to this resource.  bit.ly/expandaword

node.text:
This is how I group my students for remediation and it’s great for test prep groups/remediation. These formatives are a quick easy way to assess my math students. I created these rigorous mini-math assessments (five questions, one page) for each math standard in fourth grade. A (Form B) was also created to give my students another opportunity to show growth and learning. These tools drive my instruction and small group learning all year! 
Digital version with Google Slides and answer keys included.
5th grade is also available. 😊
Direct message me for the link to my TPT store, specify if you want 4th or 5th grade. #math #mathteacher #mathassessments

node.text: I’ve always been proud to be a teacher, but I’m especially proud to be a teacher during this time with everyone in our profession doing their best for their students. I’m honored I was given the opportunity to share with TV viewers how hard all teachers continue to work and the challenges we face with distance learning. I’m excited to share this with you! ❤️ @fox35orlando

node.text:
Still one of my favorite bulletin boards! Students and teachers both have 180 opportunities each school year, so make every moment matter! This was my welcome back bulletin board outside our classroom. I wanted it displayed for Meet the Teacher and I wanted my students to know together we are going to take every opportunity to change the world!

Link to bulletin board in my profile bit.ly/180schooldays

**If you need a different amount of days for your school year, you can email me after purchasing. #backtoschool #bulletinboards #makeeverydaycount #togetherwecanmakeadifference

node.text:
Are you a READER on board? I love advertising reading! Along with any babies on board, there may be mathematicians, artists, honor roll students, and kindness spreaders!! These student recognition car tags are a smaller version of the lawn signs! 🙌

My readers eat these tags up!! You can have them earn one for finishing a book, reading a certain number of pages, exploring a new genre, completing a book talk, so many possibilities! 

Print, laminate, hole punch-fun and creative way to recognize students! PLUS... parents love driving around and bragging about their kid! 💗
Editable template included. Link to resource in profile. bit.ly/recognitioncartag #studentawards

node.text:
New year, new school, new theme boards! I’m really excited about the background colors I’m using on the black and white version. My friend Kristen @ladybugsteacherfiles used my theme boards like this and I loved hers, perfect time for me to copy! 
Using the black and white version will match any color scheme! Swipe to see the last pic of our filled up theme boards! 

We work on theme ALL YEAR! My theme boards are one of my most referenced spaces in our classroom! It’s amazing how quickly students catch on to theme and love discussing theme because of this visual! 

Here’s how it works:
We discuss theme for EVERY book we share together. The books may not end up on the same theme board each year because it depends on how convincing my students are with their evidence. After the possible themes are presented, our class votes on which one they felt was the strongest even though all the choices may be good, the one with the most votes wins.

•I don’t have a list of theme books because this resource can be used with any fictional text and many books have several possible themes. The students decide which theme is the strongest.

•Our theme boards only include books we share as a class, this way they can all provide evidence to support or refute a theme. 

This resource now includes a DIGITAL version. 🙌

Link to resource in my profile: bit.ly/themeboards #booklover #book #readingteacher #booktheme

node.text:
Another Dollar Tree idea/solution! How’s the behavior in your cafeteria? 😬😳 Do you dread picking them up in fear of the report you might get? Me too! Insert... Golden Tray Award! The first day of school we will decide together what we want our lunch behavior to look like. I do not believe in assigned seats or silent lunch, so I try to be proactive by allowing my students to come up with the expectations for themselves. If they meet this criteria each day, they can pull a stick from our giant Kerplunk (you could add an extra minute to recess, earn a point, etc.) We will bring our plate to lunch each day as a visual reminder.

Trays and stand $1 each! Best $2 you will ever spend! 🙌 I cut the vinyl letters with my Cricut. I got this genius plate idea from my friend Maribel @learninginwonderland-they use it as a school incentive, but I needed my own!! 😝 #givethemownership #dollartreeclassroom #dollartreeteacher @dollartreeclassrooms @officialcricut
